{
  "texts": [
    "Fit: A community of workers exists that fosters a sense of inclusion and mutual support/respect.",
    "Lack of fit: Decisions at work are perceived as being unfair or inequitable, including promotional, compensation, or procedural-based decisions.",
    "Fit: Evaluations, resource distribution, and compensation are perceived as fair and equitable.",
    "Leadership as a whole is seen as valuing fairness.",
    "Values Lack of fit: A gap between the organization and individual values, including a discrepancy between stated organizational values and actual practices or personal morals."
  ]
}